<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE suite SYSTEM "https://testng.org/testng-1.0.dtd">
<suite name="Suite">
	<groups>
		<run>
			<include name="smokeTest"></include> 
		</run>
	</groups>
  <test thread-count="5" name="Test">
    <classes>
      <class name="GenericOptimised.CreateProductModuleTest"/>
      <class name="GenericOptimised.OrganizationModuleTest"/>
      <class name="GenericOptimised.CampaignsModuleTest"/>
    </classes>
  </test> <!-- Test -->
</suite> <!-- Suite -->

<!--  all classes related to GenericOptimised package are  executed here in a group
smoke or regression test can be done

Group Execution = Logical filtering (by tags like smoke/regression)
Selective execution.
Run only smoke group
Runs tests belonging to specified groups (e.g., smoke, regression)	


Batch Execution = Running multiple classes together.
Sequential execution of classes
Run LoginTests + CartTests
Runs multiple test classes together in one suite	


Parallel Execution = Running tests at the same time (multi-threading).
Simultaneous execution
Run test1, test2, test3 at the same time
Runs tests simultaneously in multiple threads


-->